OL,6,FMr Fletcher described the anguish the
OL,7,Fofficer is going through at being
OL,8,Funable to rescue his wife and children.
OL,10,F"We have multiple witnesses who
OL,11,Fdescribe the anguish that he was going
OL,12,Fthrough, his inability to get in and
OL,13,Fsave his children and save his wife.
OL,15,F"He is, as you can imagine, in a very
OL,16,Fdistraught way. Sadly, lost his family
OL,17,Fat a time which is supposed to be a
OL,18,Fhappy festive period."
